# Global Playbook

This project contributes to and draws from the global playbook at `C:\dev\cursor-playbook\`.

## When to consult the playbook

- Before starting a new pattern or architecture decision, check if the playbook has relevant lessons.
- After completing meaningful work, add new lessons to the playbook's `lessons-log.md` or the relevant topical file.

## Proposal-first update behavior

- If rule updates are needed, first tell the user what updates are proposed.
- Include those rule updates in plans when plans are used.
- Keep global playbook, local repo rules, and reusable template rules aligned.

## When to add to the playbook

A lesson belongs in the global playbook if it would help on a **different project**. Examples:
- A testing pattern that caught a subtle bug
- A deployment mistake that cost time
- A UI pattern that users responded well to
- A domain modeling technique that kept code clean

Project-specific details (this app's tax brackets, file paths, account types) stay in this repo's `.cursor/rules/domain/` folder.

## Playbook files

| File | Scope |
|------|-------|
| `playbook-policy.md` | Append-only governance, safety constraints, exception protocol |
| `engineering-principles.md` | Code structure, separation of concerns, error handling |
| `testing-and-tdd.md` | TDD workflow, test design, canonical rule documents |
| `product-and-ui.md` | UX clarity, progressive disclosure, responsive design |
| `domain-modeling.md` | Business rule encoding, waterfall patterns, projections |
| `data-and-persistence.md` | Storage layers, sync, migrations, defaults |
| `deployment-and-ops.md` | Hosting, CI/CD, DNS, env vars |
| `ai-collaboration.md` | Rule layering, test-first with AI, plan-before-implement |
| `lessons-log.md` | Chronological specific lessons |
